  "text": "Enasidenib effectively suppressed 2-hydroxyglutarate production, thus releasing myeloid blasts from differentiation block [CITATION_1] . As an orally administered drug, it produced complete response (CR) and complete remission with incomplete hematologic recovery (CRi) in 26.6% of patients, with a distinct toxicity profile, the most important being IDH inhibitor-associated differentiation syndrome [CITATION_2] .",
